keywords: ["Urban Heat Island", "Precipitation", "Coastal Cities", "Climate Change", "Meteorology"]
abstract: |
  Urban Heat Islands (UHI) are known to modify local microclimates. This study 
  investigates the relationship between UHI intensity and convective 
  precipitation patterns in three major coastal cities: Miami, Houston, and 
  New Orleans. Our results indicate a significant increase in late-afternoon 
  rainfall frequency and intensity downwind of urban centers, particularly 
  during the summer months.
